&lt;p&gt;在 &lt;code&gt;DW_AT_location&lt;/code&gt;  处  &lt;code&gt;DW_OP_fbreg&lt;/code&gt;  记录了相对某个给定的 stack frame 的偏移 (说是就是 rbp 然后 ± 一点 offset，但是我没找到)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DW_OP_fbreg operation provides a signed LEB128 offset from the address specified by the location description in the DW_AT_frame_base attribute of the current function. (This is typically a “stack pointer” register plus or minus some offset. On more sophisticated systems it might be a location list that adjusts the offset according to changes in the stack pointer as the PC changes.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
